It's a good CD - but it's a very average "vanilla" release that we see from so many new, young (and sometimes groomed) artists. There are some cool songs...but this is a very "safe" album, and it feels kinda "kiddy" high school with the puppy love songs. As far as her singing, she's obviously a great singer but only a few songs really showcase how powerful her voice is. 

This is a good CD at the end of the day, though.
